org.apache.polygene.library.sql.generator.implementation

Class TypeableImpl<ImplementedType extends Typeable<?>,RealImplementedType extends ImplementedType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.polygene.library.sql.generator.implementation.TypeableImpl<ImplementedType,RealImplementedType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ImplementedType - The base type for API interface or class.
    RealImplementedType - The actual, possibly extended in other project, type of API interface or class. This is useful when one has a complex and extendable type hierarchy and wants the implementation class to be extendable as well.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Typeable<ImplementedType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DecimalImpl, NumericImpl, SQLCharImpl, SQLFloatImpl, SQLIntervalImpl, SQLSyntaxElementBase, SQLTimeImpl, SQLTimeStampImpl, UserDefinedTypeImpl

    public abstract class TypeableImpl<ImplementedType extends Typeable<?>,RealImplementedType extends ImplementedType>
extends Object
implements Typeable<ImplementedType>
    This is base class for all classes implementing sub-types of Typeable. It is meant to be extended by actual domain-specific classes implementing the API interfaces/classes inherited from Typeable. For simple usecases, typically <ImplementedType> and <RealImplementedType> are both the same.

        public static final <T> boolean bothNullOrEquals(T one,
                                                 T another)
        Helper method to check that either both arguments are nulls, or one is non-null and equals to another. Note that this method fails if one.equals(another) fails when another is null.

        Parameters:

        another - Second object to check.
        Returns:
